body: It's wordplay. The title in Japanese is 陰キュバス (inkyubasu), with 陰 being pronounced as "in," instead of being fully written in katakana as インキュバス. Though, 陰 has a variety of different meanings, so I can't really tell you which is the correct one in this scenario with my own understanding. Guessing from how she wanted to use the toys on her ass, it could be the "behind/back" meaning.
